What is Azure DevOps 

1. Azure DevOps kya hai?
- Microsoft ka end-to-end DevOps platform hai.
- Ismein code likhne se lekar deploy karne, test karne, aur monitor karne tak sab kuch ek jagah hota hai.
- Pehle iska naam Visual Studio Team Services (VSTS) tha, phir Team Foundation Server (TFS), ab Azure DevOps.

2. Demo/Walkthrough is section mein:

a) Azure DevOps Organization banana:
- dev.azure.com pe jaake login karte hain (Microsoft account se)
- Ek Organization create karte hain — yeh aapki company/team ka top-level container hai.
- Organization ka naam unique hota hai (jaise techtutorialswithpiyush)

b) Azure DevOps Project banana:
- Organization ke andar Projects hote hain.
- Har project ek alag application/product ke liye hota hai.
- Project create karte waqt visibility select karte hain: Private (sirf team dekh sake) ya Public.
- Version control select karte hain: Git (distributed) ya TFVC (centralized — purana Microsoft wala).

c) Pricing Model:
- Azure DevOps Services (Cloud/SaaS):
- Free tier: 5 users tak free, unlimited private Git repos, 1800 minutes/month CI/CD pipeline time
- Paid: Extra users ke liye per-user charge, aur extra pipeline minutes ke liye
- Azure DevOps Server (On-Premises):
- Apne khud ke servers pe install karte hain
- Licensing alag hoti hai — usually enterprise companies use karte hain jinko data apne paas rakhna ho

d) Hosting Options — Services vs Server:
- Azure DevOps Services: Microsoft manage karta hai, cloud pe hai, maintenance nahi karna padta, globally available.
- Azure DevOps Server: Apne data center pe, khud manage karna padta hai, air-gapped/network isolated environments ke liye best.